VTechnology preserves past
p3
sVnews
p4
VViotrix Technologoies Private Limited is promoting multi-media CD RoMs in the areas of art and architecture. Set up in 2003, it focuses on heritage collections that are now spread over the whole of the southern region and parts of North India. It soon plans to have audio-visuals on heritage collections covering the entire country. The firm uses personal experiences in archiving its material. The recent set of CD RoMs brought out by them are user friendly with interactive presentations. They are designed with the combination of text, illustration and audio, helping the user in accessing information on any particular heritage site. The multi-media CDRoMs are a good asset to historians, libraries, schools and art lovers.The company has some fine Heritage Collections and audio-visuals on Mahabalipuram (Rs. 190), Ruins of Vijayanagara (Rs. 300), Mahabalipuram-Thanjavur (Rs. 300), Temples of Tamil Nadu (Rs. 590), Hoysala's Kesava Temple at Belur (Rs. 300), Temples of Imperial Cholas (Rs. 250), Glorious Hoysala's &#151;  Halebid (Rs. 300), Aihole &#151;  The Western Chalukyas (Rs. 250), Badami &#151;  The Early Western Chalukyas (Rs. 250), and Pattadakal &#151;  The Early Western Chalukyas (Rs. 250). The CD RoMs will provide complete information on each heritage site that will include the site's history, when it came up, whether any form has changed over time and the royalties which patronised the sites. The CDRoMs are more or less complete dossiers on each site.For more information and availability of the CDRoMs, contact the company at 196/3, Green Field Apartments, TNHB Flats, R30A, Ambattur Industrial Estate Road, Annanagar West, Chennai  -   01. You can call Sainath Reddappa, Managing Director, Viotrix on 98402-20333 or e-mailemail@viotrix.comand visitwww.viotrix.comThe audio-visuals are available at Landmark, Gangarams, Crossword and Fabmall.Bottom Template Starts
